rComments: Hali Kil gives the air of confidence but her lectures are a disaster. She "reads" pedagogy but the course was a disaster. Her tests were beyond difficult, like impossible. The averages were so low. When not a single uoft student can pass her matching questions it is not the students, it is the professor...

Hali is quite approachable and provides great feedback. The lecture content is dry but the group assignment was quite refreshing and fun. You will have to work a little harder than usual as her tests are tough, so be thorough with the readings and lecture slides. Her friendly personality makes up for the tough grading so it is possible to do well.
